  "type": "mcq",
  "stem": "<p class=\"stem_paragraph \">A clothing store is having a sale on shirts and pants. During the sale, the cost of each shirt is $15 and the cost of each pair of pants is $25. Geoff can spend at most $120 at the store. If Geoff buys <span class=\"italic\">s</span> shirts and <span class=\"italic\">p</span> pairs of pants, which of the following must be true?</p>\n",
